{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Uvb1x9kXj19hy7X5uvkVSv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# VCS\n     2→.git/\n     3→\n     4→# Maven\n     5→.mvn/\n     6→**/.mvn/\n     7→mvnw\n     8→mvnw.cmd\n     9→**/mvnw\n    10→**/mvnw.cmd\n    11→target/\n    12→**/target/\n    13→pom.xml.tag\n    14→pom.xml.releaseBackup\n    15→pom.xml.versionsBackup\n    16→pom.xml.next\n    17→release.properties\n    18→dependency-reduced-pom.xml\n    19→buildNumber.properties\n    20→\n    21→# IDE / Editor\n    22→.vscode/\n    23→**/.vscode/\n    24→.zed/\n    25→**/.zed/\n    26→.idea/\n    27→**/.idea/\n    28→*.iml\n    29→*.ipr\n    30→*.iws\n    31→\n    32→# OS\n    33→.DS_Store\n    34→**/.DS_Store\n    35→Thumbs.db\n    36→ehthumbs.db\n    37→\n    38→# Logs / temp\n    39→*.log\n    40→*.tmp\n    41→*.temp\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a3e41a8f-87c2-49bd-995b-2b11c28e9d8b","uuid":"b3793e3a-c343-4f79-a5f2-a9efb2289c62"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Ch3v65GNbbJUZJH7v3umfC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me analyze the migration requirements:\n\n**Current State:**\n- Spring Boot 3.3.7 with JoinFaces 5.5.6 (JSF integration)\n- Already using `jakarta.persistence.*`, `jakarta.enterprise.*`, `jakarta.inject.*`, `jakarta.faces.*` imports\n- Using Spring repositories, `@Service`, `@Component`, `@Autowired`, `@Transactional`\n- H2 in-memory database\n- JSF (Primefaces) web frontend\n- Server port 8081\n\n**Migration Target: \"jakarta\"** - This means migrating from Spring Boot to a pure Jakarta EE application. The key migration involves:\n1. Replace Spring Boot with a Jakarta EE runtime (e.g., Open Liberty, Payara, WildFly, or TomEE)\n2. Replace Spring Data JPA repositories with standard Jakarta Persistence EntityManager\n3. Replace Spring annotations (`@Service`, `@Component`, `@Autowired`, `@Transactional`) with Jakarta CDI equivalents\n4. Replace Spring Boot configuration with Jakarta EE configuration\n5. Update build to produce a WAR for a Jakarta EE runtime\n\nLet me update my plan and start the migration:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":760,"cache_read_input_tokens":48447,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":760,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":729},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a3e41a8f-87c2-49bd-995b-2b11c28e9d8b","uuid":"3fa2b812-f855-4037-960d-2e9e5903de5d"}
